"title": "5023: image of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5023",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Humanity is created in the image or likeness of God. This image of God, given in creation, was damaged in the fall, but may be restored through Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Humanity created in God's image</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:27\">GEN 1:26–1:27</a></strong> <em>Image and likeness are probably synonymous terms in Hebrew parallelism. No physical likeness between God and humanity is intended.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:1-Gen5:2\">GEN 5:1–5:2</a></p>\n<h3>Paul implies that the divine image is associated in the first place with men</h3>\n<p>Although Paul at points seems to imply that the image of God is especially associated with males, he does not imply that this involves male supremacy:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:7\">1CO 11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:11-1Cor11:12\">1CO 11:11–11:12</a></p>\n<h3>Respect for human life in God's image</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:6\">GEN 9:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:9\">JAS 3:9</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The divine image implies partnership with God in the stewardship of creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26\">GEN 1:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:3-Ps8:8\">PSA 8:3–8:8</a></p>\n<h3>The divine image includes imitating God's love and justice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:48\">MAT 5:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:17-Deut10:19\">DEU 10:17–10:19</a></p>\n<h2>The image of God disfigured, though not totally destroyed, in the fall</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23\">ROM 3:23</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Fallen humanity in contention with creation</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:17–3:19</a></p>\n<h3>Fallen humanity and the exploitation of nature</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:6-Deut22:7\">DEU 22:6–22:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:23-Isa7:25\">ISA 7:23–7:25</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ the image of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6\">PHP 2:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15\">COL 1:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:4\">2CO 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>He is the exact representation of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>He reveals God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:18\">JHN 1:18</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is the perfect human being</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:4\">JHN 1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:9\">JHN 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:7\">PHP 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17\">HEB 2:17</a></p>\n<h2>Restoration of the divine image through Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>The divine image is renewed in all who are united with him by faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:29\">ROM 8:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:13–1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:22-Eph4:24\">EPH 4:22–4:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:9-Col3:10\">COL 3:9–3:10</a></p>\n<h3>The promise of complete restoration in the future</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:49\">1CO 15:49</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:2\">1JN 3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:42\">1CO 15:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:45-1Cor15:48\">1CO 15:45–15:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:21\">PHP 3:21</a></p>\n<h3>The Christian life as a process of transformation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a></strong></p>",
